"The Bronze Age is a time period characterized by the use of bronze, proto-writing, and other early features of urban civilization."
- from Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia

the goal: to free newbies (in any area) from the burden of the past and showcase projects attempting to drag computing from the stone age.
let us match and compare the projects and see where they can really replace the legacy.

A lot of work has been done. Lets use it. Dont learn bash, learn fish. use a semantic-aware terminal. Get a selection of the
best languages and IDEs.

roadmap:
select projects, create installation scripts
hunt down tutorials and links to videos
try creating a wholesome desktop experience


