C:
===
Lets use clang as a little example here. The vision is to create a desktop full of these
things, where the state of the art tools jump out at users. The goal is that when
you think about programming in C, you start in this folder, not on google that tells
you to install gcc and CodeBlocks and assures you C is the best language for ANY PROJECT EVER!
So we could have a folder on the desktop called "C".
* a link to a clang tutorial
* an install script for http://www.jetbrains.com/clion/
* an install script for http://mbeddr.com/
* valgrind
...










